      "content": "i get that, but my coach is saying that one of those positions is basically just a way to ignore human suffering while the other is based on actual universal rights. if u had to pick one that aligns better with \"global ethics,\" wouldn't it be the asylum side? it feels like the border security argument is just a way to avoid the moral reality of people's lives.",
